25 "§ 15A-534. Procedure for determining conditions of pretrial release.
26 …
27 (h) A bail bond posted pursuant to this section is valid for a period of not more than three
28 years in any case in which a pending forfeiture has not been issued and is effective and binding
29 upon the obligor throughout all stages of the proceeding in the trial division of the General Court
30 of Justice until the entry of judgment in the district court from which no appeal is taken or the
31 entry of judgment in the superior court. In order to be relieved of the bail bond obligation, the
32 surety must notify the district attorney 30 days prior to the date the bond is set to expire. At any
33 time within 30 days prior to the date the bond is set to expire, or if the district attorney receives
