27 "§ 15A-545. District attorney submission of defendant information into nationwide
28 database.
29 For purposes of the effective implementation of this Article, each district attorney shall ensure
30 that the information of a criminal defendant that fails to appear in court is provided to the National
31 Crime Information Center within 10 days of the failure to appear in court so that this information
32 may be available nationwide."
33 SECTION 1.(b) For purposes of electronic filing pursuant to Article 26 of Chapter
34 15A of the General Statutes, the district attorney for each county and the attorney for each county
35 board of education shall be listed in the county's electronic filing or case management system as
36 parties and shall each have the burden of maintaining current contact information in that
37 electronic filing or case management system.
38 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 58-71-1 reads as rewritten:
39 "§ 58-71-1. Definitions.
40 The following definitions apply in this Article:
41 …
42 (8b) Residential address. – The defendant's address of record or any other dwelling,
43 home, building, or rental that the defendant may occupy as lodging.
44 …."
45 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 58-71-40 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
46 "(a1) No electronic system shall act in the capacity of a professional bondsman, surety
47 bondsman, or runner or perform any of the functions, duties, or powers prescribed for
48 professional bondsmen, surety bondsmen, or runners under this Article."
49 SECTION 2.(c) G.S. 58-71-200(a) reads as rewritten:
50 "(a) In order to assist licensed sureties and their agents in evaluating potential and current
51 clients for the purposes of bail, the Administrative Office of the Courts shall provide any
